******
[5] Surveillance in domestic animals
Date: Wed 17 Apr 2013
Source: CCTV (China Central Television), Xinhua News Agency report [edited]
http://english.cntv.cn/20130417/106942.shtml


Animal infections of the H7N9 avian flu have only been detected in live poultry markets and a single wild pigeon, agricultural authorities said Wednesday [17 Apr 2013].

Of the 47 801 samples collected from more than 1000 poultry markets, habitats, farms, and slaughterhouses across the country, 39 samples have tested positive for the virus, the Ministry of Agriculture said in a statement.

Of the 39 positive samples, 38 came from live poultry markets in east China's Jiangsu and Zhejiang provinces, central China's Anhui Province and the city of Shanghai.

A wild pigeon tested positive for the virus in Jiangsu [see OIE notification, item 1 above].

The virus has not been detected in pigs, the ministry said.

[Editor: Wang Xiaomei]

